{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We're going to go on a dive\nto the deep sea,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and anyone that's had\nthat lovely opportunity"},{"time":7000,"text":"knows that for about\ntwo and half hours on the way down,"},{"time":9705,"text":"it's a perfectly positively\npitch-black world."},{"time":12424,"text":"And we used to see the most mysterious\nanimals out the window"},{"time":15440,"text":"that you couldn't describe:"},{"time":16827,"text":"these blinking lights -- a world\nof bioluminescence, like fireflies."},{"time":20450,"text":"Dr. Edith Widder -- she's now at the Ocean\nResearch and Conservation Association --"},{"time":24607,"text":"was able to come up with a camera"},{"time":26390,"text":"that could capture some\nof these incredible animals,"},{"time":28900,"text":"and that's what you're seeing\nhere on the screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31300,"text":"That's all bioluminescence.\nLike I said: just like fireflies."},{"time":34217,"text":"There's a flying turkey under a tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36496,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37530,"text":"I'm a geologist by training."},{"time":40702,"text":"But I love that."},{"time":43000,"text":"And you see, some of the bioluminescence\nthey use to avoid being eaten,"},{"time":46453,"text":"some they use to attract prey,"},{"time":48000,"text":"but all of it,\nfrom an artistic point of view,"},{"time":50775,"text":"is just positively amazing."},{"time":52200,"text":"And a lot of what goes on inside --"},{"time":54000,"text":"There's a fish with glowing eyes,\npulsating eyes."},{"time":56358,"text":"Some of the colors\nare designed to hypnotize,"},{"time":59000,"text":"these lovely patterns."},{"time":61081,"text":"And then this last one,"},{"time":63000,"text":"one of my favorites, this pinwheel design."},{"time":66000,"text":"Just absolutely amazing,\nevery single dive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"That's the unknown world,\nand today we've only explored"},{"time":72087,"text":"about 3 percent\nof what's out there in the ocean."},{"time":74837,"text":"Already we've found\nthe world's highest mountains,"},{"time":77467,"text":"the world's deepest valleys,"},{"time":79000,"text":"underwater lakes, underwater waterfalls --"},{"time":81101,"text":"a lot of that we shared\nwith you from the stage."},{"time":83411,"text":"And in a place\nwhere we thought no life at all,"},{"time":86100,"text":"we find more life, we think,\nand diversity and density"},{"time":88700,"text":"than the tropical rainforest,"},{"time":90207,"text":"which tells us that we don't know\nmuch about this planet at all."},{"time":93256,"text":"There's still 97 percent,"},{"time":94609,"text":"and either that 97 percent is empty\nor just full of surprises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97734,"text":"But I want to jump up to shallow water now"},{"time":99809,"text":"and look at some creatures\nthat are positively amazing."},{"time":102519,"text":"Cephalopods -- head-foots."},{"time":105301,"text":"As a kid I knew them as calamari, mostly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107376,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108477,"text":"This is an octopus."},{"time":109700,"text":"This is the work of Dr. Roger Hanlon\nat the Marine Biological Lab,"},{"time":112901,"text":"and it's just fascinating\nhow cephalopods can,"},{"time":115100,"text":"with their incredible eyes,\nsense their surroundings,"},{"time":117678,"text":"look at light, look at patterns."},{"time":119478,"text":"Here's an octopus moving across the reef,"},{"time":122000,"text":"finds a spot to settle down, curls up\nand then disappears into the background."},{"time":126265,"text":"Tough thing to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128892,"text":"In the next bit, we're going\nto see a couple squid."},{"time":131300,"text":"Now males, when they fight,"},{"time":132997,"text":"if they're really aggressive,\nthey turn white."},{"time":135198,"text":"And these two males are fighting."},{"time":136800,"text":"They do it by bouncing\ntheir butts together,"},{"time":138897,"text":"which is an interesting concept."},{"time":140541,"text":"Now, here's a male on the left\nand a female on the right,"},{"time":143300,"text":"and the male has managed\nto split his coloration"},{"time":146000,"text":"so the female only always sees\nthe kinder, gentler squid in him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149077,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"Let's take a look at it again.\nWatch the coloration:"},{"time":156000,"text":"white on the right, brown on the left."},{"time":159000,"text":"He takes a step back,"},{"time":161735,"text":"he's keeping off the other\nmales by splitting his body,"},{"time":164473,"text":"and comes up on the other side --"},{"time":166200,"text":"Bingo!"},{"time":167288,"text":"Now, I'm told that's not not just\na squid phenomenon with males,"},{"time":170365,"text":"but I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171639,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"Cuttlefish. I love cuttlefish."},{"time":174922,"text":"This is a Giant Australian Cuttlefish."},{"time":176810,"text":"And there he is,\nhis droopy little eyes up here."},{"time":180909,"text":"But they can do\npretty amazing things, too."},{"time":183262,"text":"Here we're going to see\none backing into a crevice,"},{"time":186000,"text":"and watch his tentacles --"},{"time":188000,"text":"he just pulls them in,\nmakes them look just like algae."},{"time":191000,"text":"Disappears right into the background."},{"time":194345,"text":"Positively amazing."},{"time":195691,"text":"Here's two males fighting."},{"time":197115,"text":"Once again, they're smart enough,\nthese cephalopods;"},{"time":199600,"text":"they know not to hurt each other."},{"time":201200,"text":"But look at the patterns\nthat they can do with their skin."},{"time":204100,"text":"That's an amazing thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207519,"text":"Here's an octopus."},{"time":208820,"text":"Sometimes they don't want\nto be seen when they move,"},{"time":211276,"text":"because predators can see them."},{"time":212810,"text":"This guy can make himself\nlook like a rock,"},{"time":214910,"text":"and, looking at his environment,"},{"time":217110,"text":"can actually slide across the bottom,"},{"time":219129,"text":"using the waves and the shadows\nso he can't be seen."},{"time":222130,"text":"His motion blends\nright into the background --"},{"time":226000,"text":"the moving rock trick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228798,"text":"So, we're learning\nlots new from the shallow water."},{"time":231300,"text":"Still exploring the deep,\nbut learning lots from the shallow water."},{"time":234501,"text":"There's a good reason why:"},{"time":235788,"text":"the shallow water's full of predators\n-- here's a barracuda --"},{"time":238724,"text":"and if you're an octopus or a cephalopod,"},{"time":240800,"text":"you need to really understand\nhow to use your surroundings to hide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"In the next scene, you're going to see\na nice coral bottom."},{"time":246801,"text":"And you see that an octopus\nwould stand out"},{"time":248865,"text":"very easily there if you couldn't\nuse your camouflage,"},{"time":251472,"text":"use your skin to change color and texture."},{"time":253597,"text":"Here's some algae in the foreground --"},{"time":256000,"text":"and an octopus."},{"time":258775,"text":"Ain't that amazing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261847,"text":"Now, Roger spooked him,\nso he took off in a cloud of ink,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and when he lands, the octopus says,\n\"Oh, I've been seen."},{"time":269000,"text":"The best thing to do is to get\nas big as I can get.\""},{"time":271501,"text":"That big brown makes his eyespot very big."},{"time":274000,"text":"So, he's bluffing.\nLet's do it backwards."},{"time":276001,"text":"I thought he was joking\nwhen he first showed it to me."},{"time":278601,"text":"I thought it was all graphics.\nSo here it is in reverse."},{"time":281286,"text":"Watch the skin color;\nwatch the skin texture."},{"time":283500,"text":"Just an amazing animal,\nit can change color and texture"},{"time":286200,"text":"to match the surroundings."},{"time":287558,"text":"Watch him blend right into this algae."},{"time":290000,"text":"One, two, three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296765,"text":"And now he's gone, and so am I.\nThank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300765,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}